  "prompt": "What are the best questions to ask people to evoke wisdom?",
  "response": "Eliciting wisdom from others involves asking questions that prompt reflection, insight, and deep thinking. Here are some effective questions to consider:\n\n1. **Experiences and Lessons:**\n   - What has been one of the most significant experiences in your life, and what did you learn from it?\n   - Can you share a mistake you made and how it helped you grow?\n\n2. **Perspectives and Values:**\n   - What values are most important to you, and how do they guide your decisions?\n   - How do you define success, and has that definition changed over time?\n\n3. **Problem-Solving and Decision-Making:**\n   - How do you approach solving complex problems?\n   - What advice would you give to someone facing a difficult decision?\n\n4. **Life and Personal Growth:**\n   - What habits or practices have contributed most to your personal growth?\n   - How do you stay motivated and inspired during challenging times?\n\n5. **Relationships and Interactions:**\n   - What have you learned about building and maintaining meaningful relationships?\n   - How do you handle conflicts or disagreements with others?\n\n6. **Facing Challenges:**\n   - What strategies have you used to overcome adversity?\n   - How do you deal with uncertainty and change?\n\n7. **Legacy and Impact:**\n   - What kind of legacy do you hope to leave behind?\n   - How do you think your actions today will impact the future?\n\n8. **Self-Reflection:**\n   - If you could give your younger self one piece of advice, what would it be?\n   - What do you believe is the most important thing you\u2019ve learned about yourself?\n\n9. **Purpose and Fulfillment:**\n   - What gives your life meaning and purpose?\n   - How do you find fulfillment in your daily life?\n\n10. **General Wisdom:**\n    - What is the best piece of advice you\u2019ve ever received?\n    - What do you believe is the key to a happy and fulfilling life?\n\nThese questions aim to tap into the individual's experiences, beliefs, and insights, encouraging them to share valuable wisdom that can be beneficial to others.",
